Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "paziti" in different forms and positions, with the word highlighted by a star (*) and the English translations in parentheses:

1. *Pazi* da ne padneš! (Be careful not to fall!)
2. *Pazi* kako govoriš! (Watch how you speak!)
3. *Pazi* šta radiš! (Pay attention to what you're doing!)
4. Moramo *paziti* na svoje zdravlje. (We need to take care of our health.)
5. *Pazila* sam na sat dok si bio napolju. (I kept an eye on the clock while you were out.)
6. Ona *pazi* na svoj izgled. (She takes care of her appearance.)
7. Da li si *pazio* na instrukcije? (Did you pay attention to the instructions?)
8. *Paziš* li na novac koji trošiš? (Are you careful with the money you spend?)
9. Kada *pazimo* jedni na druge, sve ide lakše. (When we look out for each other, everything goes more smoothly.)
10. Molim vas da *pazite* na svoju prtljagu. (Please take care of your luggage.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "paziti" can have various meanings such as "to be careful", "to watch out", "to pay attention", "to take care of", "to keep an eye on", etc. Therefore, the translations provided here might vary depending on the context.